main event: A spherical white object generating intense light was observed in the sky on June 17, 1963.
interesting points: The object had no tail or pulsation and appeared to be traveling northwest., It was reported to have a minimum altitude of 150 degrees and maximum of 160 degrees., It was sighted at an azimuth ranging from 60 degrees to 90 degrees elevation., The observer concluded it did not conform to known meteorological events., The naval report describes the object as creating a very intense light and traveling at high speed.
witness description: Naval personnel aboard USS Halsey Powell
